com.box.boxjavalibv2.resourcemanagers
Class BoxUsersManager

java.lang.Object
  com.box.boxjavalibv2.resourcemanagers.BoxResourceManager
      com.box.boxjavalibv2.resourcemanagers.BoxUsersManager

public final class BoxUsersManager
extends BoxResourceManager

Use this class to execute requests synchronously against the Box REST API(V2), users endpints. Full details about the Box API can be found at http://developers.box.com/docs . You must have an OpenBox application with a valid API key to use the Box API. All methods in this class are executed in the invoking thread, and therefore are NOT safe to execute in the UI thread of your application. You should only use this class if you already have worker threads or AsyncTasks that you want to incorporate the Box API into.

Get the list of all users for the Enterprise with their user_id, public_name, and login if the user is an enterprise admin. If the user is not an admin, this request returns the current user's user_id, public_name, and login.
